# Utility Function Rules

All utility/helper functions live in the `lib/` folder at the project root.

## Required file structure inside lib/

lib/
date.ts ← formatShowtime, formatDate, isShowExpired, getRelativeTime
currency.ts ← formatPrice, calculateTotal, calculateDiscount
seats.ts ← groupSeatsByRow, isSeatAvailable, getSeatLabel, parseSeatId
booking.ts ← generateBookingRef, getBookingStatusLabel, isBookingCancellable
movies.ts ← filterMoviesByGenre, sortMoviesByDate, searchMovies
api.ts ← shared fetch wrapper, error handler, response normalizer

## Rules

- Every utility must be a pure function — no side effects, no API calls, no React hooks
- Every utility must be a named export — no default exports in lib/
- Every utility must have a JSDoc comment:
  /\*\*
  - Groups a flat seat array into rows keyed by row_label.
  - @param seats - flat SeatAvailability[] from the API
  - @returns Record<string, SeatAvailability[]>
    \*/
- Never import React or any component into lib/ files
- Never import from app/ or components/ inside lib/
- lib/api.ts is the only file allowed to make fetch calls

## When to extract to lib/

- Any array .map() / .filter() / .sort() with business logic inside a component → move to lib/
- Any date formatting → move to lib/date.ts
- Any price calculation → move to lib/currency.ts
- Any seat-related transformation → move to lib/seats.ts
